text: Why don’t crabs celebrate Christmas? Because they’re shellfish.
What’s every parent’s favorite Christmas carol? Silent Night.
What do snowmen eat for breakfast? Frosted Flakes.
Why did Santa go to music school? To improve his wrapping skills.
How do sheep say Merry Christmas? Fleece Navidad!
What did one snowman say to the other? Do you smell carrots?
Why was the Christmas tree so bad at knitting? It kept dropping its needles.
What do you call an elf who sings? A wrapper!
Why did the Christmas tree get promoted? It had all the right branches covered!
What do you call people who are afraid of Santa Claus? Claustrophobic!
Why was the Christmas ornament stressed at work? It was hanging by a thread!
How does a snowman get to work? By “icicle”!
Why did the gingerbread man fail his job interview? He crumbled under the pressure.
What do you call a workplace that runs out of coffee during Christmas? A silent night!
Why did the office computer hate Christmas? It couldn’t handle the “cookies”!
What do you call an elf who loves spreadsheets? Excel-ent!
Why did Santa refuse to work in HR? He didn’t want to deal with “naughty” lists!
How do snowmen send their Christmas cards? By “ice-mail”!
Why did the Christmas lights file a complaint? They felt they were being kept in the dark!
Why does Santa’s team always meet deadlines? They have great “elf-discipline”!
Why did Santa hire an engineer? To optimize his sleigh’s gift-to-weight ratio!
What do engineers call Santa’s workshop? A high-efficiency production line!
Why was the Christmas light display so impressive? It was a bright idea with flawless execution!
How do engineers build snowmen? With precise calculations and optimal load distribution!
What do you call an electrical engineer at Christmas? A circuit-elf!
Why did the bridge engineer miss the Christmas party? They were tied up with some tension!
Why did the engineer redesign Santa’s sleigh? To improve its aerodynamic coefficient!
Why don’t engineers decorate with tinsel? It causes too much resistance!
How do engineers wrap Christmas presents? With perfect geometric folds and minimal tape usage!
Why did the civil engineer bring concrete to Christmas dinner? They wanted to lay a solid foundation for the holiday season!
What’s Santa’s favorite engineering discipline? Reindeer dynamics!
Why was the electrical engineer’s Christmas tree so special? It had a parallel circuit of lights to avoid burnout!
What’s an engineer’s favorite Christmas drink? Ohm-made eggnog!
Why do engineers love the holiday season? It’s the only time they can take a load off without compromising safety factors!
What’s an engineer’s least favorite part of Christmas? Wrapping gifts without a blueprint!
What did Frosty’s girlfriend give him when she was mad at him? The cold shoulder.
What do snowmen eat for breakfast? Ice crispies.
What does Santa suffer from if he gets stuck in a chimney? Claus-trophobia!.
How do you know when Santa’s around? You can always sense his presents.
What does Santa suffer from if he gets stuck in a chimney? Claus-trophobia!.
What was Santa's favorite subject in school? Chemis-tree!
What do Santa’s little helpers learn at school? The elf-abet.
How much did Santa pay for his sleigh? Nothing — it was on the house!
What do snowmen call their offspring? Chill-dren
What did the beaver say to the Christmas Tree? Nice gnawing you
Who delivers Christmas presents to sharks? Santa Jaws.
What kind of motorbike does Santa ride? A Holly Davidson!
What do reindeer hang on their Christmas trees? Hornaments.
What is the best Christmas present? A broken drum, you just can’t beat it.
